ng the necessary 50 percent of votes in sunday's presidential race to avoid a runoff signe depicts the corruption repression and institutional manipulation wade has committed to this young electoral democracy impressing on the international community the urgency of supporting and defending senegal's democratic traditions related links landry signe postdoctoral scholar 2011 2013 html+ the new york times strangling democracy in senegal http www nytimes com 2012 02 25 o search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest ethiopia's embarrassing elections stage managed elections in the east african country deliver a fourth term for meles zenawi abebe gellaw wall street journal on may 31 2010 cddrl visiting scholar named young global leader march 5 2010 cddrl announcement obama advisor cddrl director mcfaul to square off against mccain advisor former cia director jim woolsey october 10 2008 cddrl news cddrl scholar talks to kqed forum about violence in zimbabwe june 24 2008 cddrl in the news kqed forum cddrl visiting scholar hicham ben abdallah interviewed on al jazeera in english video+ cddrl ard in the news al jazeera on october 3 2007 cddrl has concluded its third year of the stanford summer fellows on democracy and development program august 30 2007 cddrl draper hills summer fellows program news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
